“My brain isn’t the model. It houses and creates it?”

That maps onto a major distinction people debate in neuroscience and philosophy.

One framing:

* Brain = physical substrate (neurons, chemistry, electrical signaling, body integration)
* Model = internal representations / predictions / abstractions / learned structures generated by the system
* Mind = depending on framework, either the process emerging from the substrate, the experience layer, or the total active modeling machinery

In your framing:

brain ≠ model
brain → creates + updates + runs model

Which is a coherent position.

Though some people would push even further:

body + senses + environment + social context + memory + brain → jointly shape the model

The model isn’t just “stored.”

It’s continuously generated and updated.

